{"TopicId":29733,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Change Flag mid-flight?","CreatedByName":"Canopus","CreatedById":57774,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-28T11:11:49Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Canopus","CreatedById":57774,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-28T11:11:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIs there a way to edit the persistence file in order to change the flag of a specific mission?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KasperVld","CreatedById":40700,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-28T12:44:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYes, open the persistent.sfs (or quicksave.sfs) and right at the top there\u0027s this bit:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003EGAME\u003Cbr\u003E{\u003Cbr\u003E\tversion = 0.20.0\u003Cbr\u003E\tTitle = default (Sandbox)\u003Cbr\u003E\tDescription = No description available.\u003Cbr\u003E\tMode = 0\u003Cbr\u003E\tStatus = 1\u003Cbr\u003E\tscene = 5\u003Cbr\u003E\tflag = Squad/Flags/default\u003C/pre\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Moon Goddess","CreatedById":57446,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-28T12:57:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThat\u0027s for the whole program, I think he was asking about a mission flag.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hocki","CreatedById":33039,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-28T13:00:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYou open your quicksave.sfs, and scroll down to you find the command pod for the mission. There you change the flag, and reload \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"capi3101","CreatedById":59027,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-28T13:20:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIs it necessary to change the persistence file to change the flag? I ask because I\u0027ve had Jeb on a Gilly mission since 0.19...\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Canopus","CreatedById":57774,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-28T13:51:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThank you guys \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alephzorg","CreatedById":2383,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-29T19:33:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThank you.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMy guys who started their missions in 0.19 won\u0027t feel left out anymore.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-06-01T12:47:19Z\u0022 title=\u002206/01/2013 12:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002211 yr\u0022\u003EJune 1, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by Alephzorg\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eforgot a word, makes more sense now\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"XerZin","CreatedById":68342,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-30T10:41:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHow do I open a .sfs file? Dont have any program to do it, dont have any external programs for this.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGoogle is your friend, notepad\u002B\u002B I hope this work\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-05-30T10:47:30Z\u0022 title=\u002205/30/2013 10:47  AM\u0022 data-short=\u002211 yr\u0022\u003EMay 30, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by XerZin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"togfox","CreatedById":17083,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-30T10:43:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIts a text file. Just use notepad or equiv.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}